&nbsp;A bus transporting local school children has crashed on the R603 near Adams College in the south coast. On scene paramedics have confirmed that a total of 73 scholars between the ages of 8-12 have sustained minor to moderate injuries.Paramedics arrived at the scene and found the bus lying on its side on the side of the road. The occupants from the bus had already climbed out of the vehicle and were found walking all around the scene.&#8220;All injured children have been stabilised and since been removed from the scene and transported to various Durban hospitals for further medical care. The fire department, Metro police and several paramedics were in attendance,&#8221; said Rescue Care&#8217;s Garrith Jamieson.Cause of accident is unknown at this stage, however police are currently investigating.